MELECHDSP UI RUNBOOK — PLUGIN_UI_TEMPLATE_V1
Project: Any new MelechDSP plugin
Scope: UI bootstrapping

================================================================
GLOBAL RULES
================================================================

Obey 00_SYSTEM_RULES.txt.

UI ONLY.
No DSP or engine work.

================================================================
OBJECTIVE
================================================================

Create a new plugin UI that:
- Matches AnalyzerPro structure
- Uses mdsp_ui design system from day one
- Avoids future refactors

================================================================
STEP 0 — SESSION SETUP
================================================================

Context:
AnalyzerPro is the reference UI.

Rules:
- Copy structure, not visuals
- Reuse patterns, not code blindly

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 1 — CREATE MAINVIEW SCAFFOLD
================================================================

TASK:
Create MainView as a pure layout container.

Required:
- MainView derives from juce::Component
- No DSP logic inside MainView
- No parameter ownership

Layout regions (as needed):
- Header
- Footer
- Center view
- Optional meter rails
- Control rail

Rules:
- Layout uses ui_.metrics() only
- No magic numbers
- No setSize()

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 2 — UI CONTEXT INJECTION
================================================================

TASK:
Wire mdsp_ui::UiContext into the new UI.

Required:
- PluginEditor owns UiContext
- MainView receives UiContext&
- All UI components receive the same reference

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 3 — PLACEHOLDER VISUALS
================================================================

TASK:
Implement placeholder visuals until DSP is ready.

Rules:
- Use simple drawing
- No optimization work
- No design polish

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
END OF RUNBOOK
================================================================
